OL,3,CFormer Co-op bank boss ordered to pay
OL,4,C#184,000 or face jail
OL,6,F"He stole a large amount of money from
OL,7,Fher, depriving charities and her niece
OL,8,Fof gifts that were bequeathed to them.
OL,9,FWe are pleased to have secured a
OL,10,Fcompensation order that will right
OL,11,Fthat wrong.
OL,13,F"Flowers took advantage of Margaret
OL,14,FJarvis's illness; he knew she wouldn't
OL,15,Frealise he was stealing and even
OL,16,Fcontinued to steal from her after her
OL,17,Fdeath.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G4/6
